      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but why is that the case though? like, doesn't the second one convey the exact same information? i'm trying to understand if the distinction is just about word choice, or if there's an underlying assumption that certain ways of speaking are inherently less \"intellectual\" than others. like, if a scholar spoke like Sample B in a lecture, how would people actually judge them? would they assume they just don't know the material well enough?",
